column1: There are 10 types of people in the world: those who understand binary and those who don't.
How many programmers does it take to change a light bulb? None. It's a hardware problem.
Why did the developer go broke? Because he used up all his cache!
Why do programmers confuse Halloween with Christmas? Because 31 OCT = 25 DEC.
Why was the JavaScript developer sad? Because he didn't Node how to Express himself.
In order to understand recursion, you must first understand recursion.
Why do Java developers wear glasses? Because they can't C#.
What do you call 8 hobbits? A hobbyte!
What's a programmer's least favorite Pixar movie? A Bug's Life.
I would tell you a UDP joke, but you might not get it.
Why did the geek add body { padding-top: 1000px; } to his Facebook profile? He wanted to keep a low profile!
Why did the computer cross the road? To get a byte to eat!
What's a computer's favorite snack? Microchips!
How did the boy break the school computer? His PE teacher told him to kick the ball in the net!
A clean house is a sign of a broken computer!
Why was the computer cold? It left its Windows open!
What do you call a computer superhero? A Screen Saver!
How do you stop an Internet troll? Seize their memes of production!
Why did Wi-Fi and the computer get married? Because they had a connection!
What did the computer do at lunchtime? Had a byte!
How many bytes does it take to make a joke? Just one, but it has to be well-formed!
Why was the mobile phone wearing glasses? Because it lost its contacts!
What do you call an iPhone that sleeps too much? Dead Siri-ous!
Why did the computer sneeze? It had a virus!
Where do computers go to dance? The disk-O!
What is the biggest lie anyone can tell? "I have read and agreed to all the terms and conditions."
How did Microsoft Office get so famous? Due to good Word of mouth!
What kind of books grow on trees? Apple MacBooks!
What's a programmer's favorite hangout place? The Foo Bar!
If you put a million monkeys on a million keyboards, one of them will eventually write a Java program; the rest will write Perl programs!
Why did the scarecrow win an award? Because he was outstanding in his field!
Why don't scientists trust atoms? Because they make up everything!
What do you call fake spaghetti? An impasta!
Why did the bicycle fall over? Because it was two-tired!
What did one wall say to the other wall? I'll meet you at the corner!
Why can't you give Elsa a balloon? Because she will let it go!
What do you call cheese that isn't yours? Nacho cheese!
How does a penguin build its house? Igloos it together!
Why did the cookie go to the hospital? Because it felt crumby!
What do you call a bear with no teeth? A gummy bear!
Why did the golfer bring two pairs of pants? In case he got a hole in one!
What do you call an alligator in a vest? An investigator!
Why did the math book look sad? Because it had too many problems!
How do you organize a space party? You planet!
What's orange and sounds like a parrot? A carrot!
Why did the stadium get hot after the game? All of the fans left!
What do you call a fish wearing a bowtie? Sofishticated!
Why don't skeletons fight each other? They don't have the guts!
What did the janitor say when he jumped out of the closet? Supplies!
Why was the broom late for school? It swept in!
